records.addlTxt: Defendant Johnathon Henry Baker in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 11:14 a.m.  State advises Def will waive prelim and proceed to plea and sentencing. Court reviews atty rights, finds Def understands and waiver freely made. Court reviews prelim rights, finds Def understands and waiver freely made. Court finds probable cause. Information filed. Copy received, reading waived. Agreement stated - plea to ct 1, ct 2 dismiss, setence withheld, 1 yr probation, AODA, costs. Def agrees. Def admits prior conviction. Plea to ct 1 - guilty. Court reviews constitutional and trial rights. Factual basis. Finds Def understands, accepts plea and finds guilty of possession of THC 2nd. Ct 2 dismissed. Def has nothing to say. Court accepts agreement. Sentence withheld, 1 yr probation, AODA, costs. DNA sample and surcharge. Apply bond. Def advised of voting and firearms rights. Postconviction rights.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
